# execute()

**Instance Method**

Executes the fetch request against the managed object context that is associated with the current queue.

## Declaration

```swift
func execute() throws -> [ResultType]
```

## Discussion

Calling `execute` on an [doc://com.apple.coredata/documentation/CoreData/NSFetchRequest] will cause the [doc://com.apple.coredata/documentation/CoreData/NSFetchRequest] to run against the managed object context ([doc://com.apple.coredata/documentation/CoreData/NSManagedObjectContext]) that is associated with the queue on which the `execute` is called.
